<TITLE> Court frames charges against Atiqullah Khan Masud </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 3 (bdnews24.com) -- Charges were framed Monday in a tax evasion case against Janakantha editor and chairman of Globe Constructions Atiqullah Khan Masud and members of his family. Judge Tanjila Ismail of Special Judge's Court-6 framed the charges. The court said depositions in the case would be taken from March 10. Also accused in the case are Masud's wife Shamima A Khan and their two sons Mishal Atiqullah Khan and Jishal Atiqullah Khan. Atauddin Khan and Abdul Khaleque, the owners of two audit firms which worked for Globe Constructions, have also been implicated in the case. National Board of Revenue deputy tax commissioner Ayesha Siddiqa Shelley filed the case on Jan 6. According to the case details, the accused conspired to conceal the income of Globe Constructions to the tune of Tk 5.37 crore in the tax years 1999 to 2006. They are also accused of evading Tk 2.08 crore of tax. The Janakantha editor was arrested by joint forces from Janakantha Bhaban in Eskaton on March 7. All others accused in the case remain on the run. The same court is currently hearing the trial of another case of tax evasion against Masud. bdnew
